Citation.sTitle: Enthalpies of dilution of aqueous solutions of n-butanol, butanediols, 1,2,4-butanetriol, and 1,2,3,4-butanetetrol at 298.15K
Citation.sAbstract: Enthalpies of dilution of aqueous solutions of 1-butanol, butanediols, 1,2,4-butanetriol and 1,2,3,4-butanetetrol (erythritol), were measured at 298.15 K, using a LKB flow microcalorimeter. Experimental data were treated according to the McMillan Mayer theory, to obtain the enthalpic interaction coefficients. The pair interaction coefficient hxx shows a clear dependence on number and position of OH groups. Results are discussed in terms of molecular interactions.
